<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000i, 9100i, 9200i, 9400i, 9900i MODELS - Starting 03/01/1999 - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Some of the service to the heating and air conditioning system is performed inside the Blend-Air unit
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602302">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Perform the following procedure to remove and install the
                Blend-Air unit cover:
            </para>
            <figure id="f1602302" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602302A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Blend-Air Unit Components (Sleeper Version Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEATER CORE MOUNTING NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUNK BLEND-DOOR ACTUATOR (Sleepers Only)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BUNK BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY (Sleepers Only)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. EVAPORATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. FILTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. CAPILLARY TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. THERMOSTATIC SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. BLOWER SPEED RESISTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. BLOWER SPEED RESISTOR HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. BLOWER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. CAB BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY MOUNTING NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. CAB BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. BLOWER ASSEMBLY MOUNTING NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. CAB BLEND-DOOR ACTUATOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x1602313">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602324">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1602324" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602318.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Blend-Air Unit Top Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove top cover mounting screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from the Blend-Air unit.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x1602314">
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602324">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install top cover on the Blend-Air unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
